      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Monitor podcasts for new episodes with Taddy to Slack\n\n## Who's it for\nPodcast enthusiasts, content curators, and marketing teams who want to stay updated on new episodes from their favorite podcasts.\n\n## How it works\nThis workflow checks daily for new episodes from a list of podcasts you're monitoring. When a new episode is published, it sends a formatted notification to your Slack channel with the episode title, description, and listen link.\n\n## Requirements\n- Taddy API account (sign up at taddy.org)\n- Slack workspace with incoming webhook or bot token\n- Self-hosted n8n instance (required for community nodes)\n\n## How to set up\n1. Install the Taddy community node from Settings > Community Nodes\n2. Add your Taddy API credentials\n3. Configure your Slack credentials\n4. Update the \"Podcast UUIDs\" in the Set Fields node with your podcasts\n5. Adjust the schedule trigger timing as needed\n\n## How to customize\n- Change notification destination (email, Discord, Teams, etc.)\n- Add filtering by genre or keyword\n- Store episodes in a database for trend analysis",
        "height": 688,
        "width": 928
      },
